#Text=Curry : Senator , did you violate caucus rules of secrecy ?
#Text=I did not .
#Text=And the saying that I take great great umbrage with is ...
#Text=the only way I can fully defend myself would be to go violate caucus protocol and confidence .
#Text=Now I do n't accuse Senator Long of lying ; that is a little strong .
#Text=There are some — because what has been said to the media , particularly by Senator Long — that have had the wrong perception that I may have violated a confidence of the caucus .
#Text=I certainly want to clear up any kind of misunderstanding with my caucus mates .
#Text=But in no way did I violate a caucus confidence .
#Text=The tweet that I put out was based upon my own information , from my own whip count that I kept on this project .
#Text=Senator ( Scott ) Schneider knew about my whip count .
#Text=Senator Dennis Kruse knew about my whip count .
#Text=Senator Mike Young knew about my whip count .
#Text=And so this idea that I violated a caucus confidence is unfortunate , it 's wrong , it 's untrue , it 's misleading , and , hopefully , this will help correct that record .
#Text=Senator , Chad Tew here .
#Text=Who leaked the information about your punishment to the media ?
#Text=That is a great question because [ laughs ] —
#Text=There is another issue over in the House of Representatives about caucus confidence being violated .
#Text=I do n't know if you are following that with the whole nursing moratorium issue —

#Text=But it was interesting because the following Thursday I was called in to Senator Long and there were a couple of other senators , and they brought me in there to tell me what my consequence from this whole event was going to be .
#Text=And they listed out four different things that were going to happen , and they then told me they were going to go to the caucus and privately tell them what was going to happen .
#Text=Well , I get home Thursday night , that night , getting ready to have dinner , and I get a call from a Channel 13 WTHR NBC News affiliate .
#Text=And they say " Senator Delph , we understand this , this , this and this are going to happen to you because of violating caucus protocol .
